snippet.title: Petition To Remove Amber Heard From Aquaman 2 Has Over 1 Million Signatures [Updated]
snippet.description:
Subscribe I n  News English YouTube Channel To All The Big News Of The World.

A petition to remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2 reaches over 900K signatures. Heard first appeared as Mera, the princess of Xebel, one of the underwater kingdoms, in Zack Snyder's Justice League in 2017. She went on to reprise her role opposite Jason Momoa in 2018's Aquaman, now the highest-grossing DC movie of all time. Heard is set to return for Aquaman 2 in 2022.

Heard has lately been the center of a controversy with ex-husband Johnny Depp. Depp and Heard, who met on the set of the 2011 film The Rum Diary, married on Depp‚Äôs private island in the Bahamas in 2015. After filing for divorce in 2016, Heard obtained a restraining order against Depp, accusing him of physically and verbally abusing her. Other allegations against the actor included Depp trying to have Heard fired from Aquaman and prevent her from being hired on other Warner Bros. projects. All of the troubling allegations led to criticism over Depp being cast as Grindelwald in the Fantastic Beasts films in 2016. Depp sued Heard for defamation in 2019, after she wrote an op-ed for The Washington Post claiming to be a victim of domestic violence during their short-lived marriage. Depp also sued the U.K. publication The Sun after they called him a "wife-beater" in one of their articles. The case went to trial in July, and last Monday the judge ruled against Depp, stating that he belied there was enough evidence to support Heard's claims. Shortly after, Depp announced that he was asked to resign from Fantastic Beasts 3, with the studio confirming he would be recast.

snippet.title: Amber Heard arrives at court for libel trial
snippet.description:
(16 Jul 2020) AMBER HEARD ARRIVES AT COURT FOR LIBEL TRIAL
Amber Heard arrived at Britain's High Court Thursday (15 JULY 2020) for ex-husband Johnny Depp's libel claim against a UK tabloid.
Depp is suing News Group Newspapers, publisher of The Sun, and the paper's executive editor, Dan Wootton, over an April 2018 article that called him a "wife-beater." 
He strongly denies abusing Heard.
Depp and Heard give wildly differing accounts of their volatile relationship, which began after they met on the set of the 2011 comedy ‚ÄúThe Rum Diary.‚Äù They married in Los Angeles in February 2015. 
Heard filed for divorce the following year, and the divorce was finalized in 2017.
In court Wednesday, Heard's former personal assistant claimed that she told the model-actress about a violent sexual assault she had endured, only for Heard to ‚Äútwist" the story for her own use.
¬†¬†
Kate James said she had told Heard that she was raped at machete-point in Brazil about 25 years ago.
¬†¬†
She said she was shocked to learn that in a witness statement, Heard misrepresented and exploited the incident.
¬†¬†
‚ÄúShe referred directly to a violent rape that occurred to me 26 years ago and she twisted it into her own story and she used it for her own use," James said by video link from Los Angeles.
¬†¬†
‚ÄúI am a sexual violence survivor and that‚Äôs very, very serious to take that stance if you are not one," she added.
¬†¬†
Heard is due to give evidence in the case later this week.
